        </did>
        <scopecontent>
          <p>The Topical File contains material on topics of specific interest to Manning. Within this series, there is material concerning the confirmation of Edward Mooney as a Cardinal in February 1946. Manning was assigned to Rome to cover the story, which he considered one of the greatest of his career. Other files in the Topical File concern the Detroit Historical Society, the Detroit Metropolitan Building Fund, the Detroit Round Table of Catholics, Jews and Protestants (responsible for the holding of an annual Brotherhood Week in Detroit), Historical Preservation, and the Sleeping Bear Dune National Lakeshore.</p>
