          <p>Writings includes six chapters of an account of Manning's life as a newspaperman, a folder of magazine articles, a scrapbook of Manning's earliest newspaper work, mostly obituaries and small stories (ca. 1915), later clippings of Manning's editorials and columns, and a travel journal kept by Manning during a Pacific cruise (1930) and a European tour (1937). As in Correspondence, this series emphasizes the years 1960-1963, when nearly every column Manning wrote is included.</p>
